Interface ISafeGettable<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Superinterfaces:
    IGettable<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IAltFuture<IN,OUT>, IReactiveValue<T>, IRunnableAltFuture<IN,OUT>, ISettableAltFuture<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAltFuture, AbstractAltFuture.OnCancelledAltFuture, CompoundAltFuture, ImmutableValue, OnCancelledAltFuture, OnErrorAltFuture, PersistentValue, ReactiveInteger, ReactiveLong, ReactiveString, ReactiveValue, RunnableAltFuture, SettableAltFuture

    public interface ISafeGettable<T>
extends IGettable<T>
    Create the actual URL at the last minute, just before the request is processed.

    This may be useful for load balancing between servers or late-prioritizing parameters based on current conditions. For example use this in association with a Collection to prioritize if/which-next at that moment based on current user interface state.

    Your implementation must be thread safe since multiple WORKER threads may attempt to start network connections simultaneously. The simplest way to do this is mark the method synchronized

    Return null if no URL should be loaded at this time. Depending on your use case this may signal the end of a collection of URLs to be downloaded.
